Class OracleSemIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.jena.util.iterator.NiceIterator
      • oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena.OracleSemIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator, org.apache.jena.util.iterator.ClosableIterator, org.apache.jena.util.iterator.ExtendedIterator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OracleTripleIterator

    public class OracleSemIterator
extends org.apache.jena.util.iterator.NiceIterator
    This class extends NiceIterator. As a performance optimization, data is only retrieved upon request. Because of this, OracleSemIterator is able to handle a large result set.
    Since:
    Aug 2007

      • retrieveNodeFromRS

        public static org.apache.jena.graph.Node retrieveNodeFromRS(java.sql.ResultSet rs,
                                                            int colStartIdx,
                                                            java.lang.String projColWidth,
                                                            OracleTranslator translator)
                                                     throws java.sql.SQLException
        This method returns a Jena Node object based on the projected column values (applies to MDSYS networks).
        Parameters:
        rs - an open JDBC result set, must not be NULL.
        colStartIdx - start column index to read values and construct the Node object from.
        projColWidth - a string denotes the number of columns to read in order to construct the Node object. This value can be OracleSemQueryPlan.CONST_TWO_COL (for RDF resources at the subject or predicate position) or OracleSemQueryPlan.CONST_FIVE_COL (for RDF resources at the object position).
        translator - an instance of OracleTranslator to perform necessary escape/unescape
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • retrieveNodeFromRS

        public static org.apache.jena.graph.Node retrieveNodeFromRS(java.sql.ResultSet rs,
                                                            int colStartIdx,
                                                            java.lang.String projColWidth,
                                                            OracleTranslator translator,
                                                            java.lang.String networkOwner,
                                                            java.lang.String networkName)
                                                     throws java.sql.SQLException
        This method returns a Jena Node object based on the projected column values.
        Parameters:
        rs - an open JDBC result set, must not be NULL.
        colStartIdx - start column index to read values and construct the Node object from.
        projColWidth - a string denotes the number of columns to read in order to construct the Node object. This value can be OracleSemQueryPlan.CONST_TWO_COL (for RDF resources at the subject or predicate position) or OracleSemQueryPlan.CONST_FIVE_COL (for RDF resources at the object position).
        translator - an instance of OracleTranslator to perform necessary escape/unescape
        networkOwner - the semantic private network owner (if null then MDSYS is assumed)
        networkName - the private network name (supported from from 19c)
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • setGracefulTimeout

      • setGuide

        public void setGuide(java.util.List guide)
        Sets a guide to help navigate through all columns from RDF MATCH query result set. A guide is a list (sequence) of elements. Each element can be either OracleSemQueryPlan.CONST_FIVE_COL or OracleSemQueryPlan.CONST_ZERO. CONST_FIVE_COL means that the bound variable has 5 columns, and CONST_ZERO means the bound variable has 2 columns.

      • setHitTimeoutAlready

      • setNetworkInfo

        public void setNetworkInfo(java.lang.String networkOwner,
                           java.lang.String networkName)
        Sets the network information. From 19c private network is supported in schems other than MDSYS. On previous versions all network models are stored under MDSYS schema
        Parameters:
        networkOwner - private network owner. If null, then MDSYS is assumed
        networkName - private network name (applies to non-MDSYS schemas)
